Dr Luca Kozma

Bio

My name is Luca Kozma and I am a lecturer in psychology at the University of the West of Scotland.

My research interests include social perception, first impressions, and how gender role endorsement might affect partner choice and gendered behavior.

In my spare time I like to do sports, I enjoy knitting, reading sci-fi and mystery novels, and listening to literary podcasts. I also sing in two choirs.

I am the UK Reproducibility Network Local Network Lead for UWS.
